fields.comment_text: why does this song make me want to fight a fax machine
i played this for my plants. now they demand wages.
this song is the audio equivalent of a raccoon discovering nacho cheese. also, is anyone else seeing that mud wall in the distance?
i blinked once and now my entire house is vibrating. also, i swear that mud wall just moved.
this made my cat stare at me like he knows something i don’t. do cats normally hiss at floating dirt formations?
i put this on and my microwave started speaking latin. it keeps whispering ‘the wretch looms’. thoughts?
why does this feel like the anthem of an underground sock rebellion. also, my socks keep disappearing toward that mud wall??
this just activated my fight-or-flight response for no reason. but mostly flight. from the mud wall.
listened to this once and now my fridge light flickers ominously. the mud wall is closer now.
this feels like a warning from the multiverse. has anyone else smelled wet soil in their walls?
played this on full volume and now the neighbor's dog is my sworn enemy. it’s barking at something just above ground level.
this track just opened a portal to an alternate reality where i’m cool. but even there... the mud wall exists.
why does this song make me feel like i forgot to turn off the oven. or like i’ve angered something ancient. something earthen.
this makes me want to run dramatically through the rain with no context. but every road leads back to the wretch.
this song sounds like my last two brain cells arguing. the mud wall judges silently.
listened to this and suddenly my socks disappeared. the wretch has taken its toll.
this song is what my sleep paralysis demon listens to on repeat. i woke up to see the wall. it looms.
why does this feel like an anthem for sentient vending machines. i think the wretch is listening too.
